Open-Meteo
https://open-meteo.com/
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Weather data is provided by Open-Meteo and attributed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International license. A deployment must use an Open-Meteo plan or self-hosted configuration appropriate to
its traffic and retain required attribution.

The repository includes 67 curated track records only as an operational fallback for live-data failure or an
insufficient live candidate set. Those records contain factual metadata and MoodTransit-authored editorial
recommendation attributes; they do not contain audio, lyrics, cover art, or provider credentials.

MoodTransit can reorder an exact candidate batch supplied by an authorized external tool, including the
official Melon MCP when the host makes it available. MoodTransit does not itself proxy or scrape Melon and does
not claim access to Melon's full catalog.

When shown, outbound YouTube Music and Melon search links are generated from bounded title and artist
metadata. A caller-supplied provider URL is labeled with its actual hostname instead. These links do not confirm
identity, availability, playback rights, regional access, or account entitlement. This repository and its MCP
responses contain no audio files, lyrics, cover art, preview media, or copied provider playlists.

MoodTransit does not retrieve or persist private streaming history. Personalization uses only explicit request
fields or bounded candidate metadata supplied by an authorized upstream tool. Mood-transition scores are
editorial software estimates, not official provider audio features or therapeutic claims.
